ssjrobert</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.blackgoku.com/Contest/blackg.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/28/01 6:10:12 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.blackgoku.com/Contest/blackg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hands and Hair</span><hr size=1> I guess your right... thanx for the advice! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulinabo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LinaBo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/28/01 6:13:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.spree.com/thearts/linabo/linapic.jpg width=100 height=78></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hands and Hair</span><hr size=1> don't forget that you have a working live model constantly: yourself. this is why I have a full length mirror near my desk<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>-You can't buy love. Thank god you can buy chocolate.-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udogtopus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dogtopus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/29/01 2:32:50 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.brainfreeze.org.uk/fightclub/dogtopus.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hands and Hair</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I do that too, I find it helps loads. Hands and general poses are quite generic if you wanna see how people look. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  *notices people looking at him imagining him in the poses he's been drawing recently* Uh...*cough*... <p><a href="http://www.buttonpusher.net/kindamanga">KINDAMANGA!</a> <BR>
<a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm21.showMessageRange?topicID=148.topic&start=1&stop=20">I need guns....</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usuperrats.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Super Rats</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/29/01 10:27:15 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://imagep.webphotos.iwon.com//1000014373/1000014373_919200162004PM0.5410578.jpg width=125 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hands and Hair</span><hr size=1> With hair you really need to plan it.  To make it look good, you can't just draw strands and clums and hope it looks good.  I find the best way to plan the hair clumps is to draw direction lines for each clump.  Basically, this forces you to visualize and plan how the hair looks before you draw it.  This way you know how big to make each clump.  In general, when planning hair, pick a location on the scalp from which the direction lines begin.<br>
<br>
EDIT (add-on)<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :O --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":O"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> h yeah, one other thing.  These clumps will overlap each other.  If they don't there's something wrong.  That's one thing I notice on a lot of pictures...people trying to keep hair masses as seperate entities.  Most masses will in fact be 90% blocked off by the one in front of it. <p>Hello! <a href="http://www.superrats.net"><img src="http://imagep.webphotos.iwon.com//1000014373/307048.jpg" border="0"></a> sketchbook, fiction journal, and fun stuff -- updated weekly</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usuperrats.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Super Rats</A> at: 9/29/01 10:30:50 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uussjrobert.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ussjrobert</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.blackgoku.com/Contest/blackg.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/30/01 12:54:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.blackgoku.com/Contest/blackg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hands and Hair</span><hr size=1> I have a mirror near my desk, too. I guess i'll start using when i draw now. Using action lines o draw hair is agood idea, but i can never think of a hairdo that hasn't already been used. Does it really matter if my characters' hairdo's look like they're from DBZ or somewhere else? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwandering1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandering1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thewarp.net/war/wanderer/pi_inq2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/1/01 1:50:22 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thewarp.net/war/wanderer/infterm4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hands and Hair</span><hr size=1> It is so incredibly hard to think of something original, that you're better off using something you like.  If you combine enough un-original elements, eventually you'll pop out something new.  We all build on what has come before.<br>
